<item>
            <title>[MNG-773] profiles applied to POM inheritance hierarchy will pollute child POMs with modules from parents</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MNG-773</link>
                <project id="12316922" key="MNG">Maven (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This happens because of the merge-down-and-copy-back process which merges info into the profile to keep the dominance lines straight...this was a bad move, so it should be backed out, and a new profile merge process implemented.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
