                            <comment id="14408600" author="jdcasey" created="Mon, 22 Aug 2005 14:58:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;this effectively stops the use of settings-injected profiles within project hierarchies in which modules are used...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14408602" author="jdcasey" created="Tue, 23 Aug 2005 09:50:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MNG-773&quot; title=&quot;profiles applied to POM inheritance hierarchy will pollute child POMs with modules from parents&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MNG-773&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MNG-773&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is the root cause, but &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MNG-776&quot; title=&quot;settings.xml profile activation breaks reactor&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MNG-776&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MNG-776&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; articulates a test situation...basically any reactorized build where profiles are injected from the settings.xml&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14408536" author="jdcasey" created="Tue, 23 Aug 2005 09:51:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;NOTE: This issue should only take place when there is a POM inheritance hierarchy where multiple POMs in the hierarchy are in the same reactor build. I&apos;m closing &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MNG-776&quot; title=&quot;settings.xml profile activation breaks reactor&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MNG-776&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MNG-776&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; as a duplicate now that this note is here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
